import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    age_groups = data.groupby('age_group')['people'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.bar(age_groups['age_group'], age_groups['people'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people by age group?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Group the data by sex and sum the people column
    sex_counts = data.groupby('sex')['people'].sum()

    # Create a pie chart of the sex counts
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.pie(sex_counts, labels=sex_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')

    # Set the chart title
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of people in the dataset?', wrap=True)

    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age_group'] = pd.cut(data['age'], bins=[0, 18, 30, 45, 60, 100], labels=['0-18', '18-30', '30-45', '45-60', '60+'])
    male_data = data[data['sex'] == 'M'].groupby('age_group')['people'].sum()
    female_data = data[data['sex'] == 'F'].groupby('age_group')['people'].sum()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(male_data.index, male_data, label='Male')
    ax.bar(female_data.index, female_data, bottom=male_data, label='Female')
    ax.set_xlabel('Age Group')
    ax.set_ylabel('People')
    ax.set_title('What is the age distribution of males and females in the dataset?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['year'])
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    age_groups = ['0-14', '15-24', '25-54', '55-74', '75+']
    grouped_data = data.groupby(['year', 'age_group'])['people'].sum().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    for i, age_group in enumerate(age_groups):
        age_group_data = grouped_data[grouped_data['age_group'] == age_group]
        ax.bar(age_group_data['year'], age_group_data['people'], label=age_group, color=f'C{i}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('People')
    ax.set_title('What is the age distribution of people in each year?')
    ax.legend(title='Age Group')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
